The paper deals with the design of waveforms for robust orthogonal frequency division multiplexing (OFDM), which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses simulations, which suggests that it may fall under signal processing (cs.SP). Additionally, the paper deals with the issue of frequency offset and narrow-band interference, which are topics related to networked systems (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the parameterization of orthogonal Weyl-Heisenberg sets, which is a topic related to signal processing (cs.SI).
